<div class="guide-body">

  <h2 id="why">Why Bring Your Gym Into GLG</h2>
  <p>Gym League Global gives your members something most gyms can't offer on their own: real, structured competition against other gyms, with a season, a ladder, and bragging rights on the line. It's retention and community in one package — members who are training for a Wednesday match against a rival gym show up more, train harder, and stick around longer.</p>
  <p>You don't need to be a CrossFit box or a big-box gym to take part. Run clubs, boutique studios, and informal training crews are just as welcome — if you can field a team, you can compete.</p>

  <h2 id="setup">Getting Set Up</h2>
  <p>Registering your gym takes about five minutes:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="/signup/gym" style="color:var(--forest);font-weight:700;">Register Your Gym</a> and create your gym admin account.</li>
    <li>Select your region — if your area isn't live yet, you can still register and you'll be first in line when it launches.</li>
    <li>Name your first team (or teams — see below). You can always add more later.</li>
    <li>You're in. Your gym dashboard is ready immediately — no waiting on approval for gym accounts.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="guide-callout">
    <strong>One gym, multiple teams.</strong> If you've got the numbers, you're not limited to a single team. Plenty of gyms will field two, three, or more — split by division, by friend groups, or just by whoever signs up. Add teams anytime from your dashboard.
  </div>

  <h2 id="teams">Building Your Teams</h2>
  <p>A team needs a name and, eventually, a roster. That's it structurally — but a few practical tips from gyms who've done this before:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Name it with personality.</strong> Teams with a real identity (not just "Team A") get more buy-in from members and more engagement on social media during the season.</li>
    <li><strong>Think about division early.</strong> As GLG scales, divisions will split by fitness level and age group. Decide early whether a team is your competitive squad or your social/beginner squad — it'll shape who you recruit.</li>
    <li><strong>You don't need a full roster on day one.</strong> Create the team, open sign-ups, and build the roster over the following weeks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="roster">Managing Your Roster</h2>
  <p>There are two ways athletes end up on your team:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>They pick you directly.</strong> When athletes sign up, they can search for and select your team by name during registration.</li>
    <li><strong>You pick them.</strong> Athletes who sign up without a specific team land in your region's unassigned pool. From your gym dashboard, you can see everyone in that pool and assign them straight into one of your teams.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Your dashboard shows every athlete on every one of your teams, their contact details, and lets you move people between teams or remove them if needed — full control stays with you.</p>

  <h2 id="costs">Costs</h2>
  <p>Season 2026 registration is free while we roll out the North Shore pilot — we want gyms competing, not counting cents, while we prove out the format. A simple per-athlete season fee will apply from later in 2026 as the league scales; you'll be notified well ahead of any change, and existing gyms will never be surprised by a price change mid-season.</p>

  <h2 id="matchday">Running Match Day</h2>
  <p>On the day of your fixture:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Lineups are locked in beforehand</strong> — everyone knows which gate they're on and when, and this is displayed on-screen at the venue throughout the day.</li>
    <li><strong>Cast the display.</strong> Every fixture has a live "Cast Display" link from your Fixtures page — open it on any screen or TV at your venue. It shows the current gate, the exercise, a running timer, and both team lineups, so competitors and spectators always know what's happening and who's up next.</li>
    <li><strong>Enter results as you go</strong> (or straight after) from the Fixture Results page — points calculate automatically the moment you save.</li>
    <li><strong>The table updates live.</strong> Your region's leaderboard reflects results as soon as they're entered.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="promotion">Promoting Sign-Ups to Your Members</h2>
  <p>A few things that help gyms fill a roster fast:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Share the <a href="/guide/participant" style="color:var(--forest);font-weight:700;">Participant Guide</a> directly with members — it's written to be genuinely easy to read, not intimidating.</li>
    <li>Post your team name and sign-up link on your gym's socials and in-gym noticeboard.</li>
    <li>Run a short in-person demo of one gate so members can see what match day actually looks like before they commit.</li>
  </ul>

